{"ts": "2026-06-07T11:48:59.925332+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 890470cbcd8b22c382d09c9d7ffd222ed613ce36)", "id": "lc_535a0917-12b3-43ff-8b09-02bb3649fa8d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Apply all SQL files under migrations/ to the running pgdev container.\n# Order: filename glob, lexicographic.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\n# Note: relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\n# Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE.\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_a2c9ead7-82db-4d58-8eea-590ae4e59fc9"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5c46657e-1117-44a5-934d-a0d41db68a50", "tool_call_id": "call_00_ciOonKh0iLolvV3G09qq6000", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T11:49:05.981168+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Database Migrations Summary\n\nThis project uses **PostgreSQL 16** (via Docker) and applies plain SQL migration files in **lexicographic order** by filename (the `NNN_description.sql` convention). A container-local script `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` iterates over `migrations/*.sql` with a shell glob and pipes each file into `psql`.\n\nThere are **three migrations**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `001_create_users.sql`\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id           BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    email        TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    display_name TEXT,\n    created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n**What it does:**  \nCreates the `users` table, the core identity table.  \n- `id` – auto-incrementing `BIGINT` primary key (via `BIGSERIAL`).  \n- `email` – required, unique identifier for each user.  \n- `display_name` – optional display name (nullable).  \n- `created_at` – timestamp of row creation, defaults to current time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `002_create_sessions.sql`\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n```\n**What it does:**  \nCreates the `sessions` table to manage user authentication sessions.  \n- `id` – UUID primary key (the session token).  \n- `user_id` – foreign key to `users(id)` with `ON DELETE CASCADE` (when a user is deleted, their sessions are removed automatically).  \n- `issued_at` – when the session was created.  \n- `expires_at` – when the session expires (required, no default; the application must set this).\n\n---\n\n### 3. `003_add_session_index.sql`\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n**What it does:**  \nAdds a B-tree index on `sessions.user_id` to speed up lookups of all sessions belonging to a given user (e.g., for listing active sessions or revoking all sessions on logout/password change).\n\n---\n\n### How they are applied\n\n1. A **PostgreSQL 16** container is started via `docker compose up -d` (see `docker-compose.yml`).\n2. The script `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` runs, piping each `migrations/*.sql` file into `psql` in lexicographic order:\n   ```\n   Applying migrations/001_create_users.sql\n   Applying migrations/002_create_sessions.sql\n   Applying migrations/003_add_session_index.sql\n   ```\n3. After migrations, optional seed data from `seeds/` can be applied with `./scripts/seed.sh`.\n\nThe final schema consists of two tables (`users` → `sessions`) with a foreign-key relationship and one supporting index.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 655, "prompt_tokens": 7081, "total_tokens": 7736, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 13, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6784}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6784, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 297}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "317e13c7-ea9d-4844-9433-76efdc18fc68", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea1ea-2f95-7e92-a377-ab15a5bb68fd-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7081, "output_tokens": 655, "total_tokens": 7736, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6784}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 13}}}}]}}}
